Razgulay Group Will Increase Winter Grain Sowing 16.5% This Year

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-09-29T11:09:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/razgulay-group-will-increase-winter-grain-sowing-16-5-this-year.html
Razgulay Group (GRAZ) , a Russian producer
of sugar and grain, plans to increase its winter sowing area by
16.5 percent to 120,000 hectares (296,500 acres) this year.  About 70 percent of the area was sown with the cereals in
September, the company said in an e-mailed statement today.  Fields under wheat will cover more than 88,000 hectares,
and rye about 3,500 hectares, it said. Last year, Razgulay sowed
103,000 hectares with winter crops, according to the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
